    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-01T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-01T11:00:00-05:00" n="776"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d776">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/11171</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Willard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-01T17:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 1, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 2, 9.40 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1751. Yesterday afternoon ministerial conference took place. All members of
                    Cabinet were present except Minister of Public Instruction. <pb facs="0886"
                        n="1720" xml:id="pg_1720"/> Rumor indicates that there was a stormy session
                    respecting torpedoing of Spanish vessels especially the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Atxeri-Mendi</hi> of Bilbao which was reported in Madrid yesterday morning
                    as having been sunk by German submarine. Report confirmed in this morning’s
                    papers which state vessel was bound with coal from England to Spain and was sunk
                    off Irish coast 27th instant. Upon adjournment of Council of Ministers <hi
                        rend="italic">communiqué</hi> was given to press making public: reported
                    sinking of <hi rend="italic">Atxeri-Mendi;</hi> determination of Government to
                    secure definite facts and in the event of verification of report to put into
                    effect resolution of Council of August 10, namely, to seize a German vessel for
                    each Spanish vessel sunk; creation of a ministry of supplies with <persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_VJ1">Ventosa</persName>, former Minister of
                    Finance under Marquis of <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DAMGP1"
                        >Alhucemas</persName>, at its head.</p>
                <p>Minister of State in personal note of this date to me confirms information
                    contained in <hi rend="italic">communiqué.</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Willard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
